Classes::chapter
  Fighter::bullets
    * +1 hp/level
    * +1 dmg/level
    * Cannot use scrolls, wands, staves.
    * Can use magic weapons.
  Magic User::bullets
    * Can use scrolls, wands, staves.
    * Cannot use magic weapons.
    * Cannot use shields.
    * Can cast spells in Robes.
    * +1 spell/level (choose from one of 3 at random).
    * Magic User spells can be used once every 10 minutes per spell.
  Fighter-Mage::bullets
    * Can use wands, staves but not scrolls.
    * Can use magical one-handed weapons, but not others.
    * Can cast spells in Chain, Robes.
    * One-hand must be unoccupied to cast spells.
    * 1 spell at first level and +1 spell at every odd level.
    * +1 dmg at second level and +1 damage at every second level when attacking or for spells requiring an attack roll.
    * Fighter-Mage spells can be used once every 10 minutes per spell.


Ability Scores::chapter
  ::text
    Roll 3d6 in order.
  ::table
    ::head
      Ability | Effect
    ::row
      Strength     | 15 Strength adds +1 damage to melee and thrown attacks.
      Dexterity    | 15 Dex adds +1 to the attack roll of ranged and thrown attacks.
      Agility      | 15 Agility adds +1 AC.
      Constitution | 15 Constitution adds +0.5 hp/level (rounded up).
      Wisdom       | 15 Wisdom adds +1 to will saves.
      Intellect    | 15 Intellect grants a random spell.
      Charisma     | 15 Charisma adds +1 to the party's reaction rolls (stacks).

Saving Throws::chapter
  ::text
    Characters start at +0 in each category.

    On level up they receive 2 saving throw points that they may allocate as they choose.  They may not have more points in a category than their level.
  ::table
    ::head
      Category | Description
    ::row
      Fortitude Save  | Save against poisons, noxious fumes, etc.
      Will Save       | Save against non-physical effects such as charms.
      Reflex Save     | Save against dragon's breath, fireballs, etc.
      Perception Save | Save against a trap or illusion. Success indicates you noticed and did not trigger the trap or whatever.

